comments: Rose (NYK) moves into LaVine (CHI) and makes contact to his body and arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) makes marginal contact with Ball (CHI) as he engages with him during the pick.
Ball (CHI) places a collapsed forearm against Rose (NYK) and jumps vertically, absorbing the body contact during the driving shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) swipes down and makes contact to Randle's (NYK) arm during his putback shot attempt.
DeRozan (CHI) takes two legal steps during his hop step.
Barrett (NYK) initiates some contact with LaVine (CHI) but the contact does not affect his driving shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) jumps from point A to point B into the body of Randle (NYK), affecting his driving shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) places his off-arm against LaVine (CHI) but the contact is marginal.
The contact between Ball (CHI) and Randle (NYK) during the rebound is incidental.
DeRozan (CHI) makes a legal move prior to his jump shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Burks (NYK) commits a take foul on LaVine (CHI).
The ball is last touched by Barrett (NYK) and not LaVine (CHI) and it should be Bulls' possession.
Ball (CHI) jumps alongside of Randle (NYK) and legally contests the driving shot attempt.  The body contact is marginal.
Rose (NYK) commits a take foul on LaVine (CHI).
Green (CHI) makes marginal contact with Barrett (NYK) that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) makes contact with the ball and the ensuing contact with Randle's (NYK) arm is incidental.
Randle (NYK) commits a take foul on Green (CHI).
